    nursingActions: ["Assess adherence at every visit using validated tools (visual analog scale, pill counts, pharmacy refill data); identify barriers such as side effects, pill burden, food requirements, stigma, and substance use","Perform medication reconciliation identifying drug-drug interactions: proton pump inhibitors with rilpivirine (contraindicated) and atazanavir (avoid), rifampin with PIs (contraindicated) and dose-adjust INSTIs, metformin dose adjustment with dolutegravir","Counsel patients on regimen-specific administration requirements: rilpivirine requires a meal of ≥390 kcal; dolutegravir must be separated from polyvalent cations by 2 hours; atazanavir requires food and an acidic gastric environment","Order and interpret resistance testing at virologic failure; correlate mutations with drug susceptibility using Stanford HIVdb algorithm","Coordinate pre-exposure prophylaxis (PrEP) discussions for serodiscordant partners; prescribe tenofovir-DF/emtricitabine or long-acting cabotegravir for eligible individuals","Monitor for abacavir hypersensitivity reaction: fever, rash, GI symptoms, respiratory symptoms typically in first 6 weeks; NEVER rechallenge if suspected HSR"],
